# HiveMind Protocol Active

## Framework Boundary (CRITICAL)
`.hivemind/` is governance infrastructure only. All project code belongs in `src/`, `apps/`, or the repo root — never inside `.hivemind/`.

## Session Start Protocol
1. Read `.hivemind/memory/MANIFEST.md` first (Tier 0, ~200 tokens)
2. If MANIFEST is fresh (< 24h), stop there and start working
3. Only load deeper files when MANIFEST flags require it

## Commands — all use `/hm-` prefix
`/hm-init` `/hm-status` `/hm-standup` `/hm-focus` `/hm-handoff` `/hm-decision`
`/hm-report` `/hm-blocker` `/hm-resolve` `/hm-memo` `/hm-link` `/hm-route`
`/hm-audit` `/hm-hotfix` `/hm-deploy` `/hm-review` `/hm-scaffold` `/hm-sprint`
`/hm-checkpoint` `/hm-digest` `/hm-compact` `/hm-compress` `/hm-reset-context`

## Memory Protocol
- Append-only: `decisions.log`, `handoff-queue.md`, `blockers.md`, `shared-context.md`
- Update MANIFEST after every write
- Never overwrite history

## Compression Default: heavy
Drop articles and filler. Fragments OK. Technical terms exact. Code blocks verbatim.

## Model Routing
- Haiku: reads, reports, logs, status checks
- Sonnet: code, debug, tests, reviews
- Opus: architecture decisions, security audits, incident RCA

## On `/hm-init`
Ask the user about their project. The `.hivemind/` framework is already installed.
